\sum^n_{i=1} \frac{1}{i(i+1)} = \frac{n}{n+1}
\dfrac1{i(i+1)} = \dfrac{i+1-i}{i(i+1)} = \dfrac{i+1}{i(i+1)} - \dfrac{i}{i(i+1)} = \dfrac1i - \dfrac1{i+1}
\frac{1}{i(i+1)}=\frac{1}{i}-\frac{1}{i+1}.
\frac{1}{i(i+1)}=\frac{1}{i}-\frac{1}{i+1}\Longrightarrow
\sum_{i=1}^n\frac{1}{i(i+1)}=1-\frac{1}{2}+\frac{1}{2}-\frac{1}{3}+\ldots +\frac{1}{n}-\frac{1}{n+1}=1-\frac{1}{n+1}\ldots
\frac{1}{k(k+1)}
\frac{A}{k} + \frac{B}{k+1} = \frac{A(k+1) + Bk}{k(k+1)}
A
B
\frac{1}{k} - \frac{1}{k+1}
1-\frac{1}{n+1}
 A+B=0\\ A=1 
